### 5. **Legacy Mistral Handlers (C++ implementations)**

**Location**: `src/llama-chat.cpp` (lines 250-290)

Mistral templates defined in `llm_chat_detect_template()`:

- **Mistral V7**: Detected by `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`
- **Mistral V3 (Tekken)**: Detected by `"[INST]"`
- **Mistral V3**: Detected by `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` without spaces in `[INST]`
- **Mistral V1**: Detected by ` [INST]` (with leading space) and `' [INST] ' + system_message`

**V7/V7 Tekken format** (lines 251-265):
```cpp
for (auto message : chat) {
    if (role == "system") {
        ss << "[SYSTEM_PROMPT]" << trailing_space << content << "[/SYSTEM_PROMPT]";
    } else if (role == "user") {
        ss << "[INST]" << trailing_space << content << "[/INST]";
    } else {
        ss << trailing_space << content << "</s>";
    }
}
```

**V1/V3/V3-Tekken format** (lines 266-290):
```cpp
bool is_inside_turn = false;
for (auto message : chat) {
    if (!is_inside_turn) {
        ss << leading_space << "[INST]" << trailing_space;
        is_inside_turn = true;
    }
    if (role == "system") {
        ss << content << "\n\n";
    } else if (role == "user") {
        ss << content << leading_space << "[/INST]";
    } else {
        ss << trailing_space << (trim_assistant_message ? trim(content) : content) << "</s>";
        is_inside_turn = false;
    }
}
```

---

### 6. **Handler Function Signature Pattern**

All specialized handlers follow this pattern:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_TEMPLATE_NAME(
    const common_chat_template & tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    // 1. Message transformation (if needed)
    // 2. Apply template with adjusted messages
    data.prompt = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs, adjusted_messages);

    // 3. Set format
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;

    // 4. Mark preserved tokens
    data.preserved_tokens = { ... };

    // 5. Build PEG parser
    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        // Parser rules for content/reasoning/tool calls
        return parser_rule;
    });
    data.parser = parser.save();

    // 6. Build grammar (if tools/schema present)
    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            // Schema resolution
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });
        data.grammar_triggers = { ... };
    }

    return data;
}
```

---

### 7. **Core Data Structures**

**common_chat_params** (chat.h, lines 177-190):
```cpp
struct common_chat_params {
    common_chat_format format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    std::string prompt;
    std::string grammar;
    bool grammar_lazy = false;
    std::string generation_prompt;
    bool supports_thinking = false;
    std::string thinking_start_tag;
    std::string thinking_end_tag;
    std::vector<common_grammar_trigger> grammar_triggers;
    std::vector<std::string> preserved_tokens;
    std::vector<std::string> additional_stops;
    std::string parser;
};
```

**common_chat_templates_inputs** (chat.h, lines 158-175):
```cpp
struct common_chat_templates_inputs {
    std::vector<common_chat_msg> messages;
    std::string grammar;
    std::string json_schema;
    bool add_generation_prompt = true;
    bool use_jinja = true;
    std::vector<common_chat_tool> tools;
    common_chat_tool_choice tool_choice = COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;
    bool parallel_tool_calls = false;
    common_reasoning_format reasoning_format = COMMON_REASONING_FORMAT_NONE;
    bool enable_thinking = true;
    std::chrono::system_clock::time_point now = std::chrono::system_clock::now();
    std::map<std::string, std::string> chat_template_kwargs;
    bool add_bos = false;
    bool add_eos = false;
    bool force_pure_content = false;
};
```

**common_chat_peg_builder** (chat-peg-parser.h, lines 45-153):
```cpp
class common_chat_peg_builder : public common_peg_parser_builder {
    // Tag constants for content structure
    static constexpr const char * REASONING_BLOCK = "reasoning-block";
    static constexpr const char * REASONING = "reasoning";
    static constexpr const char * CONTENT = "content";

    // Tag constants for tool structure
    static constexpr const char * TOOL = "tool";
    static constexpr const char * TOOL_OPEN = "tool-open";
    static constexpr const char * TOOL_NAME = "tool-name";
    static constexpr const char * TOOL_ARGS = "tool-args";

    // Helper methods
    common_peg_parser tool(const common_peg_parser & p);
    common_peg_parser tool_name(const common_peg_parser & p);
    common_peg_parser tool_args(const common_peg_parser & p);
    // ... many more
};
```

---

### 8. **Flow Summary**

1. **Initialization**: `common_chat_templates_init()` loads model's chat template from GGUF or accepts override
2. **Application**: `common_chat_templates_apply()` calls Jinja template or legacy handlers
3. **Specialized Detection**: `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` checks template source for known patterns
4. **Parser Generation**: If matched, calls handler to build PEG parser + grammar
5. **Fallback**: Unmatched templates use autoparser to generate parsers automatically
6. **Parsing**: Generated PEG parser extracts reasoning, content, and tool calls from model output

---

This is a sophisticated system with good separation between Jinja-based templates (modern), legacy C++ handlers (backward compatibility), and specialized handlers for complex formats (Ministral, GPT-OSS, etc.).

